  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple national and international laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here's an overview:\n\n1. Key International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group international cooperation standards\n\n2. Domestic Legal Components\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) legislation\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n- Financial institution compliance mandates\n\n3. Typical Legal Provisions\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- International information sharing mechanisms\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Prosecution authorities\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Staff training programs\n- Internal control mechanisms\n\n6. Core Prohibited Activities\n- Concealing illegal financial proceeds\n- Transferring illicit funds\n- Disguising money's origin\n- Supporting criminal enterprises\n\nThe framework aims to disrupt financial criminal networks and protect economic systems.",
